				<div class="col-md-4">
					<h2>Ingredients</h2>
					<ul>
						<li>1 tablespoon Oil</li>
						<li>2 tablespoons Del Sur Onion Sofrito </li>
						<li>8 ounces Tomato Sauce</li>
						<li>2 cans Del Sur Beans</li>
						<li>1 1/2 cups Water</li>
						<li>Black Pepper, Garlic Powder and Oregano to Taste</li>
						<li>2 tablespoons Spanish Pimento-Stuffed Olives</li>
						<li>1/2 pound of Peeled Potatoes </li>
						<li>Combine with Del Sur Parboiled Long Grain Rice</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				<div class="col-md-8">
					<h2>Directions</h2>
					<ol>
						<li>In a medium saucepan, saut√© sofrito in oil 2-3 minutes over medium heat. </li>
						<li>Add tomato sauce, beans, and water. Season with pepper, garlic powder, oregano and stir. Broth should be slightly salty since the potatoes will absorb much of the flavor.</li>
						<li>Add potatoes and olives and bring to a boil. </li>
						<li>Reduce heat to low and simmer until potatoes are cooked through, about 30 minutes or so, depending on their size.</li>
						<li>Serve over hot rice.</li>
					</ol>
